Stop talking!

295
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:16,056
Shut up!

296
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:04,479
Answer me!

297
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:06,147
Why did you kill that child?

298
00:26:10,151 --> 00:26:12,112
<i>I don't know why I killed him either.</i>

299
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:15,991
Maybe…

300
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,495
I'm just a jerk.

301
00:26:24,082 --> 00:26:25,875
<i>Perhaps I shouldn't have lived</i>

302
00:26:27,168 --> 00:26:28,795
<i>in the first place.</i>

303
00:26:28,878 --> 00:26:32,048
<i>Serial murders in the past few months</i>
<i>have caused widespread fear.</i>

304
00:26:32,132 --> 00:26:34,175
<i>The murderer is finally caught.</i>

305
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:37,637
<i>Li Jen-yao, dubbed "The Rainstorm Killer"</i>
<i>by the media, is only 25 years old.</i>

306
00:26:37,721 --> 00:26:41,850
<i>He turned himself in to the police</i>
<i>after killing his father yesterday</i>

307
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:44,853
<i>and confessed to multiple murders.</i>

308
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:46,896
<i>Li Jen-yao,</i>
<i>who committed multiple murders,</i>

309
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,440
<i>was sentenced to death in 2017.</i>

310
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:50,483
<i>Now, six years later,</i>
<i>he still awaits execution.</i>

311
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,611
<i>Attorneys are reportedly exploring</i>

312
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:54,863
<i>a constitutional review for Li Jen-yao,</i>

313
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:57,324
<i>but Li Jen-yao has yet to sign</i>
<i>an engagement letter</i>

314
00:26:57,407 --> 00:26:59,659
<i>and has refused to file</i>
<i>an extraordinary appeal.</i>

315
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:27,187
Pin-yu?

316
00:27:29,022 --> 00:27:31,399
I remember when I first met you…

317
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:34,694
you said we were family.

318
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:38,615
You said I had forgotten a lot
because of a car accident.

319
00:27:40,575 --> 00:27:41,993
None of this is true, is it?

320
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:48,333
Tien-ching never met you.

321
00:27:48,416 --> 00:27:50,752
But you knew so much about me.

322
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:52,379
This can't be a coincidence.

323
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:54,506
Did Li Jen-yao plan it?

324
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:02,931
Did everything

325
00:28:03,890 --> 00:28:04,933
come back to you?

326
00:28:05,975 --> 00:28:07,227
Answer me first.

327
00:28:08,728 --> 00:28:10,397
When you stayed and took care of me,

328
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:12,899
did you already know

329
00:28:14,234 --> 00:28:18,113
that Li Jen-yao was going to kill
everyone who hurt Hsiao-tung?

330
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:26,246
Why didn't you stop him?

331
00:28:26,746 --> 00:28:28,373
Why did you let him do it?

332
00:28:29,332 --> 00:28:30,959
Why should I have stopped him?

333
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:32,961
If he hadn't done it,

334
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:36,047
I would've done it myself
and killed him too!

335
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:41,761
Because if it hadn't been for him,

336
00:28:43,555 --> 00:28:45,181
this wouldn't have happened to you.

337
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:49,728
He was with you back then.

338
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:53,022
But he failed to protect you
and even let this happen.

339
00:29:00,947 --> 00:29:03,199
<i>Yet, in fact,</i>
<i>I know better than anyone else</i>

340
00:29:04,367 --> 00:29:06,619
<i>that deep down, the person I hate the most</i>

341
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:09,289
<i>is myself.</i>

342
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:12,959
<i>Back then, I really wanted to contact you.</i>

343
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:15,003
<i>I really wanted to know</i>

344
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:17,922
<i>how you were doing</i>
<i>after I moved to Taipei.</i>

345
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:22,343
<i>But I was afraid to hear</i>

346
00:29:23,094 --> 00:29:26,890
<i>that you were doing well without me.</i>

347
00:29:28,224 --> 00:29:29,893
<i>I was afraid you would realize</i>

348
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:33,229
<i>that I had been missing you,</i>

349
00:29:34,022 --> 00:29:35,690
<i>that I wished we could go back to</i>

350
00:29:36,483 --> 00:29:38,401
<i>when we were together all the time.</i>

351
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:41,279
<i>But I was afraid to say it.</i>

352
00:29:42,322 --> 00:29:43,740
HSIAO-TUNG CALLING

353
00:29:47,076 --> 00:29:48,870
Hello? Hsiao-tung.

354
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:50,955
How come you're calling out of the blue?

355
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:54,292
<i>You seriously said that?</i>
<i>What's been keeping you so busy?</i>

356
00:29:54,375 --> 00:29:56,085
<i>Why haven't you called me?</i>

357
00:29:58,546 --> 00:29:59,631
Sorry.

358
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:02,300
I've had a lot of homework lately.

359
00:30:02,383 --> 00:30:04,552
I'm also taking
tutoring classes after school.

360
00:30:04,636 --> 00:30:07,180
And on weekends,
I have to help out at my mom's store.

361
00:30:07,263 --> 00:30:09,474
Why did you leave without waiting for us?

362
00:30:10,975 --> 00:30:12,227
Sorry, I forgot.

363
00:30:12,727 --> 00:30:15,104
-I'm talking to a friend. One moment.
-Okay.

364
00:30:15,605 --> 00:30:17,315
-Hey, Hsiao-tung. So…
<i>-Hey, Yun-chen.</i>

365
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:18,817
<i>It's okay.</i>

366
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:20,860
<i>I'll let you get back to your friends.</i>

367
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:22,904
<i>My dance practice is starting.</i>

368
00:30:23,404 --> 00:30:24,531
<i>We'll talk soon.</i>

369
00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:27,534
<i>I'm going to hang up now. Bye.</i>

370
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:28,660
Hey, then--

371
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:43,925
<i>That's why</i>

372
00:30:45,552 --> 00:30:48,763
<i>I pretended that I was doing well</i>
<i>on my own in Taipei,</i>

373
00:30:50,181 --> 00:30:52,809
<i>that I was living</i>
<i>a great and fulfilling life…</i>

374
00:30:54,936 --> 00:30:56,813
<i>that I'd gotten used to</i>

375
00:30:57,355 --> 00:30:59,190
<i>life without you by my side.</i>

376
00:31:02,443 --> 00:31:04,571
<i>Yet I didn't know</i>

377
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:07,657
<i>that was when it all happened.</i>

378
00:31:09,617 --> 00:31:12,078
<i>I didn't know I wasn't there for you</i>

379
00:31:12,954 --> 00:31:14,747
<i>when you needed me the most.</i>

380
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,877
<i>I didn't know anything.</i>

381
00:31:20,253 --> 00:31:21,671
<i>I didn't know any of it.</i>

382
00:31:22,297 --> 00:31:24,591
How could I not have known any of it?

383
00:31:25,174 --> 00:31:26,342
How could I…

384
00:31:27,302 --> 00:31:29,679
how could I have let you
go through that alone?

385
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:47,488
I'm sorry.

386
00:31:51,117 --> 00:31:52,368
I'm sorry.

387
00:31:55,371 --> 00:31:56,915
Hsiao-tung, I'm sorry.

388
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:02,462
I'm so sorry.

389
00:32:12,472 --> 00:32:16,351
<i>Have you ever regretted</i>
<i>the crimes you committed?</i>

390
00:32:17,852 --> 00:32:19,187
<i>I don't regret them.</i>

391
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:24,275
<i>Will you not regret them</i>
<i>even if you're executed in the end?</i>

392
00:32:25,485 --> 00:32:27,195
<i>This is what I deserve.</i>

393
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:30,823
<i>No matter what my punishment is…</i>

394
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:34,702
<i>I accept it.</i>

395
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:37,056
WE FILM PRODUCTIONS

396
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:39,058
If every person Li Jen-yao killed

397
00:33:39,726 --> 00:33:41,269
was connected to that video,

398
00:33:41,352 --> 00:33:43,187
that means his motive for murder

399
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:45,898
was to get revenge for Chiang Hsiao-tung.

400
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:48,901
Rather than revenge,

401
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:51,320
I think

402
00:33:51,946 --> 00:33:54,365
Li Jen-yao was trying
to protect Chiang Hsiao-tung.

403
00:33:54,449 --> 00:33:55,992
To protect Chiang Hsiao-tung?

404
00:33:56,075 --> 00:33:57,035
Yes.

405
00:33:57,118 --> 00:34:00,538
I think he did what he did
to protect Chiang Hsiao-tung.

406
00:34:00,621 --> 00:34:03,041
He didn't want other people to know

407
00:34:03,541 --> 00:34:06,335
that those things
happened to Chiang Hsiao-tung,

408
00:34:07,086 --> 00:34:09,422
nor did he want anything
to trigger her memory.

409
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:11,049
Hold on, Yu.

410
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:12,884
Can you first tell us

411
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:15,720
where you learned about these things?

412
00:34:15,803 --> 00:34:18,014
Like the relationship between Jen-yao
and Hsiao-tung,

413
00:34:18,097 --> 00:34:20,433
and the people who hurt her.

414
00:34:22,477 --> 00:34:23,686
How do I even start?

415
00:34:24,479 --> 00:34:25,313
Yu,

416
00:34:25,813 --> 00:34:27,440
have you found Chiang Hsiao-tung?

417
00:34:29,317 --> 00:34:30,234
What?

418
00:34:30,318 --> 00:34:31,778
Isn't she already dead?

419
00:34:31,861 --> 00:34:34,489
Didn't you two find out
about Chiang Hsiao-tung

420
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:36,532
because Yu was possessed by a ghost?

421
00:34:36,616 --> 00:34:38,326
No, listen.

422
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:40,745
If you follow Yu's train of thought,

423
00:34:40,828 --> 00:34:43,539
everything Li Jen-yao did

424
00:34:44,332 --> 00:34:46,959
was not only to avenge Chiang Hsiao-tung

425
00:34:47,043 --> 00:34:49,754
but also to protect her,

426
00:34:49,837 --> 00:34:52,006
so she wouldn't remember
those things, right?

427
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:52,965
What does it mean?

428
00:34:55,051 --> 00:34:56,677
Chiang Hsiao-tung isn't dead!

429
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:02,433
Is she still alive somewhere?

430
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:12,068
Wait.

431
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:15,446
If

432
00:35:15,947 --> 00:35:19,367
Li Jen-yao had risked so much
to hide Chiang Hsiao-tung,

433
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:21,494
he would never tell you all this.

434
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:25,123
Hsu Ta-wei.

435
00:35:29,585 --> 00:35:32,213
Hey, besides, I've watched that video.

436
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:35,133
No one else's face was shown,

437
00:35:35,758 --> 00:35:37,468
except Chiang Hsiao-tung's.

438
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:38,803
What does it mean?

439
00:35:38,886 --> 00:35:41,806
She was the only one
who could have told you about it.

440
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:48,312
Yu.

441
00:35:50,189 --> 00:35:51,357
You two have met, right?

442
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:56,612
Yes.

443
00:35:57,196 --> 00:35:58,990
Everything you just said is correct.

444
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,867
Chiang Hsiao-tung

445
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:03,494
told me all this.

446
00:36:03,578 --> 00:36:04,996
Hey, then,

447
00:36:05,872 --> 00:36:07,665
can you arrange for us to meet?

448
00:36:09,083 --> 00:36:11,085
Strictly speaking,

449
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:14,505
I'm trying to figure out
a way for you guys to meet.

450
00:36:32,148 --> 00:36:33,357
What's on your mind?

451
00:36:40,156 --> 00:36:41,365
Do you think

452
00:36:41,866 --> 00:36:43,701
what Yu said earlier

453
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:45,036
is true?

454
00:36:52,126 --> 00:36:52,960
Hey.

455
00:36:54,629 --> 00:36:55,755
Do you remember

456
00:36:56,255 --> 00:36:58,341
when we first made it
into the Taipei Film Festival?

457
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:02,011
How could I possibly forget?

458
00:37:03,221 --> 00:37:05,598
We were supposed to receive
our award that day.

459
00:37:06,098 --> 00:37:08,226
But we ended up at the police station.

460
00:37:08,809 --> 00:37:09,977
<i>What was the honk for?</i>

461
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:12,188
What was that? Get out of the car.

462
00:37:12,772 --> 00:37:15,191
Get out! Why are you being
a coward now? Get out!

463
00:37:15,274 --> 00:37:17,276
Hsu Ta-wei, you're not getting out.

464
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:19,278
I'll call the cops. Let them handle it.

465
00:37:19,362 --> 00:37:20,196
Honking nonstop!

466
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:23,366
You kept honking.
What the hell was that for? Get out!

467
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,534
-Hsu Ta-wei! You--
-Get out!

468
00:37:25,618 --> 00:37:26,827
Get out.

469
00:37:26,911 --> 00:37:28,329
Don't think I won't hit you.

470
00:37:35,419 --> 00:37:36,420
Stop!

471
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:37,964
Stop!

472
00:37:38,965 --> 00:37:39,799
Hsu Ta-wei!

473
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:42,093
Hsu Ta-wei, what are you doing?
Hsu Ta-wei!

474
00:37:43,469 --> 00:37:44,303
Hsu Ta-wei!

475
00:37:44,887 --> 00:37:46,514
Hsu Ta-wei!

476
00:37:56,691 --> 00:37:57,858
I lied to you.

477
00:37:58,734 --> 00:37:59,902
What do you mean?

478
00:38:00,403 --> 00:38:01,237
I don't get it.

479
00:38:08,703 --> 00:38:11,038
He dropped the charges against me

480
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:15,209
because after we got
to the police station,

481
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:16,669
he recognized who I was.

482
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:19,463
You knew each other?

483
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:26,804
I left the car and beat him up,

484
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:30,057
not because he blocked us in,

485
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:31,976
but because he was…

486
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:39,775
the one who raped my sister…

487
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:43,821
and drove her to suicide.

488
00:38:49,910 --> 00:38:51,620
I could never forget

489
00:38:53,289 --> 00:38:54,790
that, in court,

490
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:57,084
he knelt on the floor

491
00:38:57,877 --> 00:38:59,295
and said tearfully,

492
00:39:00,129 --> 00:39:02,048
"Please forgive me."

493
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,676
"I know I made a mistake."

494
00:39:06,886 --> 00:39:08,888
"I will turn over a new leaf."

495
00:39:15,561 --> 00:39:19,231
<i>I could never forget</i>
<i>the way my sister died.</i>

496
00:39:20,024 --> 00:39:22,234
<i>None of us said we would forgive him.</i>

497
00:39:25,196 --> 00:39:26,530
But the court

498
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:29,950
was swayed by his damn crocodile tears.

499
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:33,746
They believed he was truly remorseful

500
00:39:34,663 --> 00:39:36,374
and still had a conscience.

501
00:39:38,584 --> 00:39:40,628
Not to mention he was a minor.

502
00:39:42,463 --> 00:39:43,297
Fuck.

503
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:46,801
He… only did a few years and was released.

504
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:00,356
Since the day

505
00:40:02,024 --> 00:40:03,901
I left the courthouse,

506
00:40:04,819 --> 00:40:06,028
you know,

507
00:40:06,779 --> 00:40:08,906
I have been so angry.

508
00:40:09,407 --> 00:40:11,575
I'm still furious.

509
00:40:15,204 --> 00:40:17,248
That's why I wanted to film Li Jen-yao.

510
00:40:19,125 --> 00:40:21,252
Why film that murderer?

511
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:31,595
I was thinking that if it was
because I couldn't release my rage,

512
00:40:32,638 --> 00:40:34,849
then maybe I could use my documentary

513
00:40:36,058 --> 00:40:37,810
to let others see

514
00:40:38,727 --> 00:40:41,814
and understand the hatred inside me.

515
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:55,578
TALENTED HIGH SCHOOL BALLERINA VERSUS SIX

516
00:40:59,373 --> 00:41:02,126
TALENTED HIGH SCHOOL BALLERINA VERSUS SIX

517
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:17,558
But I could never have imagined
that the only person in the world…

518
00:41:21,228 --> 00:41:24,648
who could understand my pain

519
00:41:24,732 --> 00:41:27,776
would actually be Li Jen-yao.

520
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:26,669
Chiang Hsiao-tung, I know you can hear me.

521
00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:51,193
These past few days,

522
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:55,364
I've been watching Li Jen-yao's interview.

523
00:42:59,201 --> 00:43:01,120
I also secretly went to see your parents.

524
00:43:09,044 --> 00:43:11,130
I didn't know what was going on back then…

525
00:43:13,549 --> 00:43:15,175
so I didn't feel much.

526
00:43:16,510 --> 00:43:19,722
Now that I've experienced
everything you went through…

527
00:43:23,851 --> 00:43:25,352
seeing them

528
00:43:26,687 --> 00:43:28,355
made my heart ache.

529
00:43:34,194 --> 00:43:35,654
But I couldn't tell

530
00:43:36,864 --> 00:43:38,532
if that was your pain or mine.

531
00:43:42,328 --> 00:43:43,495
Hsiao-tung.

532
00:43:44,663 --> 00:43:45,831
Let me ask you.

533
00:43:47,249 --> 00:43:49,335
Are you sure
you don't want to see Li Jen-yao?

534
00:43:52,254 --> 00:43:54,173
Because I know you do.

535
00:43:54,673 --> 00:43:59,428
That's why you took my computer then
and looked up what happened to Li Jen-yao.

536
00:43:59,511 --> 00:44:02,556
And after learning
that he was put on death row,

537
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:04,683
you wanted to see him one last time.

538
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:07,102
Were you crying?

539
00:44:07,811 --> 00:44:09,229
<i>That wasn't me.</i>

540
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:10,648
<i>It was her.</i>

541
00:44:12,316 --> 00:44:13,525
LI JEN-YAO

542
00:44:14,318 --> 00:44:15,861
Why did she look up Li Jen-yao?

543
00:44:15,944 --> 00:44:17,988
What's their relationship?

544
00:44:21,700 --> 00:44:24,119
I don't know why you backed out later.

545
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:28,082
But I know you want to see Li Jen-yao.

546
00:44:28,832 --> 00:44:31,794
That's why you told me
all about the two of you.

547
00:44:32,544 --> 00:44:35,422
You want me to protect him and help him

548
00:44:35,923 --> 00:44:36,924
on your behalf.

549
00:44:37,716 --> 00:44:39,176
But you should know

550
00:44:39,259 --> 00:44:42,596
that, although I am happy
to face anything for you,

551
00:44:43,180 --> 00:44:44,723
there's one thing

552
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:46,850
I can never do for you.

553
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:48,811
That is…

554
00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:55,192
I'm not the person
Li Jen-yao wants to see.

555
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,296
Just like you,

556
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:18,632
all these years,

557
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:21,009
the person Li Jen-yao wants to see most

558
00:45:22,177 --> 00:45:23,470
has always been you.

559
00:45:26,181 --> 00:45:28,350
No matter how you've changed,

560
00:45:29,810 --> 00:45:31,687
he still only wants to see you.

561
00:48:35,412 --> 00:48:37,706
TO LI JEN-YAO

562
00:48:40,417 --> 00:48:44,504
CHIANG HSIAO-TUNG

563
00:48:44,588 --> 00:48:47,382
MINISTRY OF JUSTICE

564
00:50:30,277 --> 00:50:31,653
Hey, Li Jen-yao.

565
00:50:44,583 --> 00:50:47,044
LI JEN-YAO, DOCUMENTARY, INTERVIEW OUTLINE

566
00:51:16,656 --> 00:51:20,786
PLANNER: CHOU PIN-YU

567
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:38,887
It's about time. So…

568
00:51:41,890 --> 00:51:45,435
Will you… come again?

569
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,022
I will come again.

570
00:52:19,636 --> 00:52:20,595
Dummy.

571
00:52:21,888 --> 00:52:23,431
I've missed you so much.

572
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:28,019
Me too.

